# UI Design Reference

## 1. Piano Grid Editor (EditorPage)

Three-panel layout:

- **Left sidebar** (~220px, bg #1a1a2e): App logo "AMA-MIDI" (clickable, navigates to dashboard), "+ New Song" button, scrollable song list (title + note count per item, active item highlighted blue), user avatar + name + logout at bottom.
- **Main area** (flex-1, bg #0d1117): Top toolbar with editable song title, description, action buttons (Save, Share, Play/Stop, BPM control). Status bar showing pitch range, time range, note count, online users. Chromatic piano grid below.
- **Right panel** (~280px, bg #1a1a2e, conditional): Appears when a note is selected. "Edit Note" form with Title, Description, Pitch (solfège label), Time/Beat, Color swatches. Update and Delete buttons. History section showing ledger entries.

### Chromatic Piano Grid

- **X-axis (columns)**: 88 piano keys (A0–C8), labeled in chromatic solfège (Do, Do#, Re, Re#, Mi, Fa, Fa#, Sol, Sol#, La, La#, Si) with octave numbers
- **Y-axis (rows)**: Beat positions (0–299), flowing downward. Row count = 300 clickable 1-beat increments
- **Virtualized rendering**: Only visible rows (~20–30) are rendered via `@tanstack/react-virtual`
- **Black/white key distinction**: Black-key columns have a slightly darker background
- **Notes**: Colored cells at (pitch, beat) intersections
- **Click empty cell**: Places a note with snap-to-grid
- **Audio feedback**: Clicking a cell plays the corresponding pitch via Web Audio API

### Audio Playback

- Play/Stop button in toolbar
- BPM input field (configurable tempo)
- Playback uses triangle-wave oscillators with ADSR envelope
- Visual playhead indicator scrolls through beat rows during playback
- `beatsToSec = 30 / bpm` conversion for timing

## 2. Song Dashboard (DashboardPage)

- **Top nav**: Logo left (clickable to home), search bar center, user avatar right
- **Page header**: "My Songs" title, "+ Create New Song" button (blue)
- **Filter tabs**: All Songs | Shared with me | Recent. Sort dropdown on right.
- **Card grid** (3 columns, responsive): Each card (#1e293b, rounded) has mini piano grid preview thumbnail (generated from actual note data: `notePreview`), song title (bold white), bottom stats row (note count, collaborator count, last modified)

### Create Song Modal

- Modal overlay with title input, description textarea
- Creates song via API and navigates to editor

## 3. Login / Register (AuthPage)

- Centered card (~400px, bg #1a1a2e) on dark background (#0a0a1a)
- Logo "AMA-MIDI" with music note icon
- Tab switcher: Sign In | Sign Up
- Sign In: email field, password field, blue "Sign In" button
- Sign Up: name field, email field, password field, blue "Sign Up" button
- 2FA challenge: TOTP code input (6-digit) when `requires2fa` is returned from login
- 2FA setup: QR code display via `qrcode.react`, manual secret display, verification code input

